        "headerTitle": "Calculating True Cost",
        "layout": "concept-full",
        "layoutData": {
          "title": "Total Economic Cost = Explicit + Implicit",
          "paragraphs": [
            "<strong>Example: Friday Night Decision</strong>",
            "You have $30 and Friday evening free.",
            "<strong>Option A: Go to Movies</strong>",
            "â€¢ Explicit cost: $30 (ticket + snacks)",
            "â€¢ Implicit cost: $60 foregone work shift",
            "â€¢ Total economic cost: $90",
            "<strong>Option B: Work Extra Shift</strong>",
            "â€¢ Explicit cost: $0",
            "â€¢ Implicit cost: Entertainment value of movie",
            "â€¢ Earn $60, but give up fun",
            "<strong>Option C: Study for Test</strong>",
            "â€¢ Explicit cost: $0",
            "â€¢ Implicit cost: Both money AND fun",
            "â€¢ Gain: Better grade (future value)",
            "Most people only see explicit costs. Opportunity cost thinkers see the full picture.",
            "Not \"Can I afford this?\" but \"Is this the best use of my scarce resources?\""
          ],
